      "writtenOn": "2017-10-23T22:22:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "the requirement that buildbucket buckets are global causes problems, e.g. given a bucket identifier (bucket name), it is not easy to determine its project. We want to fix that problem, so that code like this does not have to be written. We are thinking to fix that by removing the \"bucket namespace is global\" requirement. It can be achieved by changing the bucket identifier from (bucket name) to (project id, bucket name), but it is a breaking change and that\u0027s why we are punting on that.\n\nFor luci buckets, we\u0027ve mitigated the problem by requiring the \"luci.\u003cproject id\u003e.\" bucket name prefix.\n\nThis CL hardens the requirement, so it would be harder to remove it in the future. I see two options:\n\n1) require project id in the configs, so I guess instead of \"\u003cbucket\u003e/\u003cbuilder\u003e\" require \"\u003cproject id\u003e/\u003cbucket\u003e/\u003cbuilder\u003e\".\n2) assume the \"luci.\u003cproject\u003e.\" prefix\n\nI prefer (1)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 45,
        "endChar": 61
      },
      "revId": "07115c18f65e186a20731b7adc1abf8c7c4dd04b",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "352fe376_94982eb4",
        "filename": "luci_notify/config/validate.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 45,
      "author": {
        "id": 1154295
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-10-23T22:56:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In order to validate that the builder really is part of that project, don\u0027t we still need to make an RPC call like this anyway for the time being?\n\nI can do (1), but then it\u0027s not really validating the bucket since someone could just put the project ID of the current project even though the builder is from a different project. Without an RPC call right now, there\u0027s no way to be sure someone isn\u0027t doing that. If buildbucket  emitted a project ID with the build information, I could then just create builder ID as you suggest, and all would be fine.\n\nWith (2) it\u0027s a little better since that can\u0027t happen, but it\u0027s not a good long-term solution and I agree will have to be replaced.\n\nI\u0027m not exactly sure what I should be doing now to get to a state where I can use luci-notify against prod buildbucket. What do you suggest? Just require project ID and don\u0027t fully validate (other than that it\u0027s there and the same as the current project)? Do (2) for now since its simple and then use project IDs later? Or should I just wait?",
      "parentUuid": "816c0dbd_f471321b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 45,
