      "writtenOn": "2017-11-01T03:46:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Let me know if you think what I\u0027ve done is satisfactory.\n\nRather than explicitly ask for a project in the configuration to validate, I just assume that the configuration\u0027s project as given by luci-config is the parent project of any Builder in the configuration. This makes adding cross-project builders easy in the future, as I can just add an optional \"project\" field to the configuration. This also saves a bunch of duplication in the configuration of the project, since we only support builders from the same project.",
